OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FA bright end
OL,6,Fto the day then a dry night with long
OL,7,Fclear spells. Becoming chilly in the
OL,8,FArgyll glens with a touch of frost and
OL,9,Fpatchy fog.
OL,10,
OL,11,CFriday:FAnother dry and bright day
OL,12,Fwith long periods of sunshine. A
OL,13,Fchilly start for many then becoming
OL,14,Fwarm by the afternoon.
OL,15,
OL,16,COutlook for Saturday to Monday:FHigh
OL,17,Fpressure will maintain the dry and
OL,18,Fsettled weather with sunshine at
OL,19,Ftimes. Feeling quite warm inland but
OL,20,Fcooler along coasts.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
